I don’t know what feeling comfortable with you around means,

546
00:41:39,766 --> 00:41:45,068
what feeling good when you see the good in me means,

547
00:41:45,589 --> 00:41:49,111
or what my heart beating fast when you take care of me means.

548
00:41:51,863 --> 00:41:52,706
Achi.

549
00:42:00,483 --> 00:42:04,309
Before this, I didn’t know what to answer you.

550
00:42:08,463 --> 00:42:14,628
But reflecting on my feelings has made me realize

551
00:42:16,731 --> 00:42:19,426
that all these things I’ve been feeling

552
00:42:20,734 --> 00:42:22,588
is not just acknowledging your feelings.

553
00:42:23,850 --> 00:42:25,411
It means...

554
00:42:27,364 --> 00:42:29,010
I have feelings for you too.

555
00:42:33,234 --> 00:42:34,515
I really like you, Karan.

556
00:42:55,008 --> 00:42:56,706
I’m not dreaming, am I?

557
00:42:59,062 --> 00:42:59,914
No.

558
00:43:01,025 --> 00:43:02,117
You’re not dreaming.

559
00:43:10,881 --> 00:43:12,109
(This is the first time)

560
00:43:13,595 --> 00:43:15,829
(I’m not hearing any voices in Karan’s head.)

561
00:43:18,228 --> 00:43:23,207
(But I can still feel how he feels anyway.)

562
00:43:28,368 --> 00:43:32,920
(Maybe I gained this magic)

563
00:43:36,136 --> 00:43:38,619
(because the angels empathize with Karan.)

564
00:43:41,503 --> 00:43:44,711
(Karan is really God’s favorite son.)

565
00:43:58,916 --> 00:44:00,614
Do you like watching the sunset?

566
00:44:01,189 --> 00:44:02,757
Do you want to watch it together this Saturday?

567
00:44:02,780 --> 00:44:03,887
What do you mean?

568
00:44:03,905 --> 00:44:04,740
Our first date.

569
00:44:05,644 --> 00:44:06,500
(Just you wait.)

570
00:44:06,521 --> 00:44:07,640
(I’ll surprise you all day.)

571
00:44:07,669 --> 00:44:09,311
(I’m going on a date. I must look handsome.)

572
00:44:09,323 --> 00:44:10,422
When you’re not wearing glasses,

573
00:44:10,438 --> 00:44:11,047
you also look cute.

574
00:44:12,251 --> 00:44:14,028
Why are you so good to me?

575
00:44:14,094 --> 00:44:15,543
Why don’t you try to look at me in a new way?

576
00:44:15,614 --> 00:44:17,371
When a man buys you a shirt,

577
00:44:17,385 --> 00:44:19,761
it means he wants to be the one to take it off.

578
00:44:19,783 --> 00:44:21,761
I want to take you somewhere quiet

579
00:44:21,857 --> 00:44:22,745
so we can be alone.

580
00:44:22,770 --> 00:44:23,486
(Huh?)

581
00:44:24,206 --> 00:44:33,576
[At the very least, Karan deserves to know that I’ve never hated him.]
